1
00:00:01,458 --> 00:00:08,666
Name: Ahmad al-Haj Abd, 27 years old, married

2
00:00:11,875 --> 00:00:15,041
I used to work in the private business sector

3
00:00:17,708 --> 00:00:20,791
Interviewer: When were you arrested by ISIS?

4
00:00:21,083 --> 00:00:28,125
Can you specify the date, which year and month?
And what were the charges brought against you?

5
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:34,875
I was arrested in 2014, I don’t remember the exact month

6
00:00:35,208 --> 00:00:43,166
Either the sixth or seventh month,
the charge was possession of a weapon

7
00:00:43,625 --> 00:00:47,083
And also the charge of collaboration, something like that

8
00:00:47,666 --> 00:00:51,000
Interviewer: How many times were you detained by them?

9
00:00:51,083 --> 00:00:56,791
Twice, the first time for one day, and the second time for 20 days

10
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:03,625
Interviewer: Describe for us what happened when
you were arrested and brought to this place

11
00:01:03,708 --> 00:01:10,708
Did you know that this place was a
prison before? Describe this place for us

12
00:01:10,958 --> 00:01:16,208
They brought us to Bourj Prison. Of course, I knew Bourj
Prison before, everyone knows it, it’s a well-known prison

13
00:01:16,875 --> 00:01:18,750
But no one could know what was inside

14
00:01:20,250 --> 00:01:25,583
There’s a door where they bring in prisoners, but they
brought me in from the other side, from another door

15
00:01:26,458 --> 00:01:31,416
Then they took us inside, to the solitary cells

16
00:01:31,458 --> 00:01:35,250
Interviewer: What did you feel when you entered the prison?

17
00:01:35,375 --> 00:01:43,875
I felt afraid of what might happen to me,
because I didn’t know what my charge was

18
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:51,208
They called me a collaborator, so honestly, I was very afraid

19
00:01:51,541 --> 00:01:53,875
Of course, anyone who enters this place feels fear

20
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,958
Interviewer: How many ISIS members brought you here?
Witness: Eight

21
00:02:02,208 --> 00:02:05,875
Interviewer: Were your hands cuffed
or your eyes blindfolded? Explain more

22
00:02:06,375 --> 00:02:13,666
When they brought me and took me in through the main gate, I
wasn’t blindfolded from the time they took me until this door

23
00:02:13,791 --> 00:02:20,500
When I entered the solitary rooms, they blindfolded me when I went in

24
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:24,083
They blindfolded me in that area, and there were eight people

25
00:02:25,375 --> 00:02:28,791
They blindfolded me and took me inside, and they put me in the interrogation room

26
00:02:30,166 --> 00:02:35,541
Interviewer: What changes took place at the entrance of the Bourj Prison?

27
00:02:35,666 --> 00:02:39,833
What was this place like before, and how has it become today?

28
00:02:40,708 --> 00:02:48,708
The tower had not been bombed before,
it didn’t have the destruction it has now

29
00:02:50,083 --> 00:02:57,416
Now, it’s the most heavily bombed building in Tabqa, the Bourj
